IConnector
public class URLConnector
extends AbstractConnector

Connector to MX via an URL with the MX Jar library (could be via web application server, rmi server or via loaded shared library).

Constructor Detail

URLConnector

public URLConnector(org.eclipse.core.resources.IProject _project,
                    String _javaPath,
                    String _mxJarPath,
                    String _url,
                    String _user,
                    String _passwd,
                    boolean _updateByFileContent)
             throws Exception
Initializes the URL connector to MX database. First the required Java classes and codec library are copied to the _project temporary directory. Then the Java process URLConnectorServer is started which handles the connection to the MX database.

Parameters:
_project - related eclipse project for which the URL connector is initialized
_javaPath - Java path
_mxJarPath - path of the MX Jar library
_url - URL of the MX server
_user - MX user
_passwd - MX password
_updateByFileContent - true if update is done with file content
Throws:
Exception - if connect to given MX server is not possible

URLConnector

public URLConnector(File _projectPath,
                    org.osgi.framework.Bundle _bundle,
                    String _javaPath,
                    String _mxJarPath,
                    String _url,
                    String _user,
                    String _passwd,
                    boolean _updateByFileContent)
             throws Exception
Initializes the connection to the MX server.

Parameters:
_projectPath - path to the project temporary folder
_bundle - bundle of the plug-in to access the class and required libraries for the server
_javaPath - path for the Java executable
_mxJarPath - path of the MX Jar library
_url - URL of the MX server
_user - name of the user on the MX server
_passwd - password of the user on the MX server
_updateByFileContent - true if update is done by transmitting the file content; otherwise false
Throws:
Exception - if connection to the MX server could not be started

disconnect

public void disconnect()
                throws IOException,
                       InterruptedException
Disconnects from the MX server.

Throws:
IOException - if the stream to the MX server could not be written
InterruptedException - if the thread sleep failed (for the loops while waiting for the exit of the process)
